[Thinking] **Updating input component**

I’m realizing that the Input component isn't forwarding refs since it doesn't use forwardRef. Since RHF needs a ref for uncontrolled inputs, the values become undefined. I need to convert it to use forwardRef and export it correctly. So, I’ll update input.tsx and apply the patch to utilize React.forwardRef and set a displayName. After making those changes, I should retest and run lints to check everything. Time to get patching!
Good catch: your `Input` component currently **doesn’t forward a ref**, which React Hook Form relies on for registering uncontrolled inputs—so the submitted values end up `undefined`. I’ll update `src/components/ui/input.tsx` to use `React.forwardRef`, then we should see values correctly captured everywhere.
