## 5. Nice-to-Have Refinements

### 5.1 No route-level code splitting

Both pages are eagerly imported in `router.tsx`. Using `React.lazy` for `DashboardPage` would be a simple but visible signal of production awareness.

### 5.2 Inconsistent export style on `TodoListsPage`

```7:38:src/features/todoLists/TodoListsPage.tsx
export function TodoListsPage() { ... }
export default TodoListsPage;
```

Both named and default exports. The rest of the codebase uses named exports consistently. Pick one.

### 5.3 `NavLink` hard-codes route union instead of using router types

```4:7:src/app/components/NavLink.tsx
interface NavLinkProps {
  to: '/' | '/dashboard';
  children: ReactNode;
}
```

TanStack Router provides type-safe route paths via the registered router type. Using a manual union defeats that benefit.

### 5.4 CSS body reset conflicts with CSS variable theming

```8:11:src/index.css
@layer base {
  body {
    @apply dark:bg-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 bg-background text-foreground;
  }
```

`dark:bg-slate-900` is a hardcoded Tailwind color that conflicts with the CSS variable `--background` approach used everywhere else. This likely overrides the `--background` variable in dark mode with an arbitrary value.

### 5.5 `useTodoListItem` includes `form` in effect deps

```23:28:src/features/todoLists/components/TodoList/TodoListItem/useTodoListItem.ts
  useEffect(() => {
    form.reset({
      name: item.name,
      description: item.description ?? '',
    });
  }, [item.id, item.name, item.description, form]);
```

The `form` object from `useForm` is stable, so including it in deps is harmless but signals uncertainty. The ESLint exhaustive-deps rule may require it, but a comment acknowledging form stability would show intentionality.

### 5.6 Unhandled promise in blur handlers

```30:38:src/features/todoLists/components/TodoList/TodoListItem/useTodoListItem.ts
  const handleNameBlur = useCallback(() => {
    const current = form.getValues('name');
    const trimmed = current.trim();
    form.trigger('name').then((valid) => {
      if (!valid) return;
      if (trimmed && trimmed !== item.name) {
        onUpdate({ name: trimmed });
      }
    });
